            <!-- 
L.iv. S reads śāsanna, while Shri reads śāsanaṁ. Shastri in his palaeographic discussion specifically notes that the anusvāra is sometimes represented in this inscription by a short horizontal stroke, and one of the loci he cites for this is line 4 of the seal, which shows that he did read naṁ here even if he prints nna in his edition. The last character is certainly not nna; it looks much like a halanta N with a line above, but the line for anusvāra is very clear in duṣkr̥taṁ in line 38 (and a halanta N would probably not have a boxhead), so I stand convinced. 
-->
